{"type":"message","id":"6c7d18a1","parentId":"7cbdb015","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:32:48.573Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Revising the Output**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm focused on refining the output for the `dm_status` command. The goal is to present information in a clear and concise format as requested by the user. I've begun modifying the code in `src/main.py` to match the specifications.\n\n\n**Formulating the Implementation**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nOkay, I'm now drafting the code for the `dm_status` command. My plan involves counting active fleet members by checking for `.pid` files related to specific applications.  I will then handle the \"Security\" status check based on the presence of the relevant folders, hardcoding \"Active\" for now. Finally, the \"Profit\" status will be set to \"Calculating...\" as per the instructions, likely as a placeholder for the future. The `src/main.py` file seems the best place to make these updates.\n\n\n**Updating the Logic**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm now in the midst of updating the `dm_status` command. My recent focus has been on replacing the existing, more verbose logic with the user's requested concise output format. I've considered the fleet member counting using `.pid` files and security checks, which I'll hardcode as \"Active\" for now. Further, I've confirmed that the bot's application logic relies on checking for the existence of PID files, as I'd anticipated. Finally, I'm verifying the replacement in `src/main.py`.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771162368567_142","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"src/main.py","oldText":"async def dm_status(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"\"\"\n    status_msg = \"📊 **Bot Status Report**\\n\\n\"\n    \n    # 1. PID / Running State\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        try:\n            with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n                pid = f.read().strip()\n            status_msg += f\"✅ **Status:** Active (PID: {pid})\\n\"\n        except:\n            status_msg += \"⚠️ **Status:** PID file error\\n\"\n    else:\n        status_msg += \"💤 **Status:** Inactive (No PID file)\\n\"\n\n    # 2. Master Protocol Version\n    version = \"Unknown\"\n    if os.path.exists(MASTER_PROTOCOL):\n        try:\n            with open(MASTER_PROTOCOL, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                # Look for Title or Version line\n                content = f.read()\n                lines = content.splitlines()\n                for line in lines:\n                    if \"Version\" in line or \"v.\" in line.lower():\n                        version = line.strip()\n                        break\n                if version == \"Unknown\" and lines:\n                     version = lines[0].strip()\n        except Exception as e:\n             version = f\"Error: {e}\"\n    status_msg += f\"📜 **Protocol:** {version}\\n\"\n\n    # 3. Evolution Log (Last Change)\n    last_change = \"None\"\n    if os.path.exists(EVOLUTION_LOG):\n        try:\n             with open(EVOLUTION_LOG, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                lines = f.readlines()\n                # Get last non-empty line\n                for line in reversed(lines):\n                    if line.strip():\n                        last_change = line.strip()\n                        break\n        except:\n            pass\n    status_msg += f\"🧬 **Last Evolution:** {last_change}\\n\"\n    \n    # 4. LangFuse (Placeholder)\n    status_msg += \"🔎 **LangFuse Traces:** Active (Monitoring)\\n\"\n\n    await update.message.reply_text(status_msg, parse_mode='Markdown')","newText":"async def dm_status(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"\"\"\n    # Fleet Status\n    fleet_apps = [\"730\", \"570\", \"440\", \"252490\"]\n    active_count = 0\n    for app_id in fleet_apps:\n        if os.path.exists(f\"src/bot_{app_id}.pid\"):\n            active_count += 1\n            \n    # Security Status (Check if critical folders exist)\n    sec_active = os.path.exists(\"D:/Dmarket_bot/specs\") and os.path.exists(\"D:/Dmarket_bot/memory/checkpoints\")\n    sec_text = \"Active\" if sec_active else \"Warning\"\n\n    status_msg = (\n        f\"✅ Fleet: {active_count} Active\\n\"\n        f\"✅ Security: {sec_text}\\n\"\n        f\"⏳ Profit: Calculating...\"\n    )\n\n    await update.message.reply_text(status_msg)"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":14390,"output":1375,"cacheRead":11930,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15765,"cost":{"input":0.02878,"output":0.0165,"cacheRead":0.002386,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.047666}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771162349999}}
