{"type":"message","id":"87ee44d4","parentId":"accee42b","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:33:10.416Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Defining Project Setup**\n\nI've established the foundational directory structure.  Specifically, I've implemented the `specs` and `checkpoints` folders within their designated paths. My attention has then shifted towards understanding the bot's core logic in `src/main.py` as a precursor to refactoring the fleet management functionality.\n\n\n**Consolidating & Finalizing**\n\nI've successfully completed the refactoring of the fleet mode functionality. The updates to `src/trading_bot.py` and `src/agent_wrapper.py` are now working as expected. Also, I've verified the `dm_status` checklist updates in the telegram bot. Finally, I've created the `MCP_INTEGRATION_PLAN.md` documentation, and now compiling my output.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"**Status: Complete**\n\nI have successfully executed the requested repairs and upgrades.\n\n### 1. Security Folders (Physical Fix)\n✅ Created directory: `D:\\Dmarket_bot\\specs`\n✅ Created directory: `D:\\Dmarket_bot\\memory\\checkpoints`\n\n### 2. Fleet Mode Refactor\nI have refactored the fleet management system to support multiple AppIDs via environment variables.\n\n*   **Modified `src/trading_bot.py`:** Now accepts `TARGET_APP_ID` from the environment (defaulting to 730) and logs its identity accordingly.\n*   **Rewrote `src/agent_wrapper.py`:**\n    *   Updated to loop through AppIDs: `[730, 570, 440, 252490]`.\n    *   Launches subprocesses with `TARGET_APP_ID` injected into the environment.\n    *   Manages PID files as `src/bot_<APPID>.pid`.\n\n**Code Diff (Summary for `src/agent_wrapper.py`):**\n```python\n# BEFORE:\nFLEET_GAMES = [\"CS2\", \"Rust\", \"TF2\", \"Dota 2\"]\n# Spawns with --game argument\n\n# AFTER:\nFLEET_APPS = [\"730\", \"570\", \"440\", \"252490\"]\n\ndef spawn_worker(app_id, pid_file):\n    env = os.environ.copy()\n    if app_id:\n        env[\"TARGET_APP_ID\"] = app_id\n    # Spawns with env var\n```\n\n### 3. UI Upgrade (Live Checklist)\nI updated the `/dm_status` command in `src/main.py` to return the requested checklist format.\n\n**New Output Format:**\n```\n✅ Fleet: 4 Active\n✅ Security: Active\n⏳ Profit: Calculating...\n```\n\n### 4. MCP & N8N Research\nI have created the integration plan at `docs_archive/MCP_INTEGRATION_PLAN.md`.\n\n**Plan Summary:**\n*   **Concept:** Use N8N as the \"Body/Senses\" (handling external APIs like Jira, Slack, Email) and OpenClaw as the \"Brain\" (logic, reasoning, local ops).\n*   **Bridge:** OpenClaw exposes an **MCP Server** (native or via `mcporter`). N8N acts as an **MCP Client** or connects via HTTP/SSE to trigger OpenClaw tools. This allows N8N workflows to delegate complex cognitive tasks to OpenClaw.","textSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":16343,"output":795,"cacheRead":15226,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17138,"cost":{"input":0.032686,"output":0.00954,"cacheRead":0.0030452,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0452712}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771162381050}}
